00:18:14.330 --> 00:18:16.970
Almeda was probably close to 80

00:18:16.970 --> 00:18:21.600
and Christie was maybe
30, early thirties.

00:18:21.600 --> 00:18:26.540
Anyway, it was a very nice
photograph and testimony.

00:18:26.540 --> 00:18:30.900
Hobart Smith, whom you saw
with the mountain banjo,

00:18:33.090 --> 00:18:35.200
also played the fiddle
and the guitar.

00:18:35.200 --> 00:18:37.460
And, in fact, when
he played the guitar,

00:18:37.460 --> 00:18:42.900
at least for one year he played 365
days while his brother preached,

00:18:42.900 --> 00:18:47.780
so that really built up
his stamina in his playing.

00:18:47.780 --> 00:18:52.030
So this is Hobart playing

00:18:52.030 --> 00:18:55.510
"John Brown Dreamed the Devil
was Dead" on the fiddle.

00:18:55.510 --> 00:19:18.110
[ Music ]

00:19:18.110 --> 00:19:21.230
And here we have Alan
with Wade Ward,

00:19:21.230 --> 00:19:25.390
one of the earliest people
that the Lomaxes found.

00:19:25.390 --> 00:19:30.970
And you can say he's listening to
his music and thrilled to do it.

00:19:30.970 --> 00:19:35.630
I was lucky enough to
be alive when I did get

00:19:35.630 --> 00:19:38.820
to meet Wade Ward and
also Bessie Jones.

00:19:38.820 --> 00:19:41.450
So those were two of the
great elders they collected

00:19:41.450 --> 00:19:48.300
from that I got to and Wade Ward
