00:48:58.850 --> 00:49:06.350
But before we do that, I want
to say that Tuesday night

00:49:06.350 --> 00:49:12.200
at the Kluge prize awards
recipient Philosophers Habermas

00:49:12.200 --> 00:49:14.590
and Taylor spoke of their
important perspectives

00:49:14.590 --> 00:49:16.890
on behalf of the humanities.

00:49:16.890 --> 00:49:21.060
As a folklorist in the discipline
I consider especially relevant

00:49:21.060 --> 00:49:27.130
to the 21st electronic and global
century, folklife offers a strategy

00:49:27.130 --> 00:49:32.640
for Habermas' communication in the
public sphere and for Taylor's view

00:49:32.640 --> 00:49:36.400
about a major challenge
for democracy.

00:49:36.400 --> 00:49:40.820
We cherish our sense of
community, our ethnicity,

00:49:40.820 --> 00:49:44.970
or perhaps our nation, for
as C. Vann Woodward said,

00:49:44.970 --> 00:49:47.940
"Our history is part
of our identity".

00:49:47.940 --> 00:49:51.680
But then how do we
approach the other.

00:49:51.680 --> 00:49:56.390
Traditional music has repeatedly
offered an impressive means

00:49:56.390 --> 00:49:58.690
for musical crossroads.

00:49:58.690 --> 00:50:01.050
Music often crosses ethnic,

00:50:01.050 --> 00:50:05.310
class and gender borders
enthusiastically rather

00:50:05.310 --> 00:50:06.870
than aggressively.

00:50:06.870 --> 00:50:09.880
In many ways, for example,

00:50:09.880 --> 00:50:13.500
African American music has
influenced the creation

00:50:13.500 --> 00:50:17.610
of perhaps each of our
Appalachian and Southern creations

00:50:17.610 --> 00:50:20.630
of American musical genres.

00:50:20.630 --> 00:50:23.530
This gradual shift from ethnic

00:50:23.530 --> 00:50:28.770 position:56%
to regional traditions may
illustrate how this process benefits

00:50:28.770 --> 00:50:33.960
various ethnic groups, and so
I think it's really important.

00:50:33.960 --> 00:50:36.850
Another thing that I
didn't mention earlier.

00:50:36.850 --> 00:50:43.350
When Alan Lomax was in Scotland,
he and some of his buddies,

00:50:43.350 --> 00:50:47.740
like Hamish Henderson,
created the public festival

00:50:47.740 --> 00:50:50.050
so that traditional
singers could have a place

00:50:50.050 --> 00:50:53.830
at the Edinburgh Festival,
not just classical things.

00:50:53.830 --> 00:50:59.070
So they were working on this effort
to be with in the public sphere.

